rComments: Really approachable and caring. He has a humble voice and attitude. He is the best physics teacher among all 3 in phy131.

A good prof. Really passionate about his work. Music and Astro class too advance unless you know all areas music theory, music creation, coding, astronomy, astronomy theory. Class goes really fast! Weekly homework quiz, assignments can be difficult if you dont understand basic coding or music creation/theory. Make-up and Bonus assignments are good

rComments: Really cool, easygoing guy. Has ratchet but effective in-lecture experiments. He makes a great effort to connect with the class he's teaching. I found him extremely helpful and willing to help students understand difficult concepts. Has fairly challenging tests, though nothing less than what is expected of a university physics course.

Dr. Russo is a very passionate physics teacher that loves to make every concept that he teaches clear to every student. Tbh, I was sad at first that Dr. Wilson wasn't teaching the course at first, but Dr. Russo was equally good. The demonstrations are amazing and he has many tools to offer when it comes to visualizing concepts. Tests are a bit hard

Easy Chili Pepper - very easy on the eyes.  Dr. Russo is refreshingly passionate about the material he teaches and ties it into interesting applications within his own field of study, astrophysics.   His office hours are fantastic and gives you all the help you could possibly need.   Tests err on the harder side.

rComments: Definitely the best lectures I had in first year, he usually incorporates a physical demonstration of the material being covered in lecture to give students a clearer understanding. The class is challenging but it's what you would expect when you sign up for physics. He is helpful when you ask him questions and is passionate about the material.
